Target.description: Closer to the target is better. Positive if the value is greater than or equal to AcceptanceRangeLowValue and lower than or equal to AcceptanceRangeHighValue. Neutral if the value is greater than or equal to ToleranceRangeLowValue and lower than AcceptanceRangeLowValue OR greater than AcceptanceRangeHighValue and lower than or equal to ToleranceRangeHighValue. Critical if the value is greater than or equal to DeviationRangeLowValue and lower than ToleranceRangeLowValue OR greater than ToleranceRangeHighValue and lower than or equal to DeviationRangeHighValue. Negative if the value is lower than DeviationRangeLowValue or greater than DeviationRangeHighValue.

Neutral if the value is greater than or equal to ToleranceRangeLowValue and lower than AcceptanceRangeLowValue OR greater than AcceptanceRangeHighValue and lower than or equal to ToleranceRangeHighValue. Critical if the value is greater than or equal to DeviationRangeLowValue and lower than ToleranceRangeLowValue OR greater than ToleranceRangeHighValue and lower than or equal to DeviationRangeHighValue. Negative if the value is lower than DeviationRangeLowValue or greater than DeviationRangeHighValue.

Minimize.description: Lower is better. Positive if the value is lower than or equal to AcceptanceRangeHighValue. Maximize.description: Higher is better. Positive if the value is greater than or equal to AcceptanceRangeLowValue. axis1.description:
General Rules for all chart types
  1. All measues with role "axis1" are assigned to feed uid "valueaxis". All measures with role "axis2" are assigned to feed uid "valueaxis2". All measures with role "axis3" are assigned to feed uid "bubbleWidth".
  2. If a chart type does not use the feed uid "valueaxis2", then all measures with role "axis2" are treated as measures with role "axis1".
  3. If a chart type requires at least 1 measure on the feed uid "valueaxis" (true for all non-"dual" chart types), but there is no measure with role "axis1", then the first measure with role "axis2" is assigned to feed uid "valueaxis"
  4. If the chart type requires at least one measure on the feed uid "valueaxis2" (true for all "dual" chart types"), but there is no measure with role "axis2", then the first measure with role "axis3" or "axis4" or (if not exists) the last measure with role "axis1" is assigned to feed uid "valueaxis2".

  2. If a chart type does not use the feed uid "valueaxis2", then all measures with role "axis2" are treated as measures with role "axis1".
  3. If a chart type requires at least 1 measure on the feed uid "valueaxis" (true for all non-"dual" chart types), but there is no measure with role "axis1", then the first measure with role "axis2" is assigned to feed uid "valueaxis"
  4. If the chart type requires at least one measure on the feed uid "valueaxis2" (true for all "dual" chart types"), but there is no measure with role "axis2", then the first measure with role "axis3" or "axis4" or (if not exists) the last measure with role "axis1" is assigned to feed uid "valueaxis2".

sap.chart.Chart.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new Chart. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getChartType chartType} : string (default: bar)
    • {@link #getUiConfig uiConfig} : object
    • {@link #getVisibleDimensions visibleDimensions} : string[] (default: [])
    • {@link #getInResultDimensions inResultDimensions} : string[] (default: [])
    • {@link #getVisibleMeasures visibleMeasures} : string[] (default: [])
    • {@link #getVizProperties vizProperties} : object
    • {@link #getVizScales vizScales} : object[]
    • {@link #getIsAnalytical isAnalytical} : boolean
    • {@link #getSelectionBehavior selectionBehavior} : sap.chart.SelectionBehavior (default: DataPoint)
    • {@link #getSelectionMode selectionMode} : sap.chart.SelectionMode (default: Multi)
    • {@link #getEnablePagination enablePagination} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getEnableStableColor enableStableColor} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getEnableScalingFactor enableScalingFactor} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getCustomMessages customMessages} : object
    • {@link #getColorings colorings} : object
    • {@link #getActiveColoring activeColoring} : object
    • {@link #getValueAxisScale valueAxisScale} : object
  • Aggregations
    • {@link #getData data} : sap.ui.core.Element[]
    • {@link #getDimensions dimensions} : sap.chart.data.Dimension[]
    • {@link #getMeasures measures} : sap.chart.data.Measure[]
  • Events
    • {@link #event:drilledDown drilledDown} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:drilledUp drilledUp} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:renderComplete renderComplete} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:selectData selectData} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:deselectData deselectData} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:valueAxisFixedScaleTurnedOff valueAxisFixedScaleTurnedOff} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:drillStackChanged drillStackChanged} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.viz.ui5.controls.common.BaseControl#constructor sap.viz.ui5.controls.common.BaseControl} can be used as well.

enablePagination.description:
Enable pagination mode. Pagination mode empowers users to visualize dataset page by page by scrolling back or forth. Currently there are some limitations of this mode in some chart transversal features, such as:
  1. Selection status might lost for new batch data
  2. Keyboard navigation will be only available for current continuous batch data
  3. Zoom out might have inconsistent behavior, Hence the gesture in mobile might have the same issue
  4. Time charts did not enable pagination yet
  5. Series color might be inconsistent before/after jump pages
Please refer to release notes for details.

sap.chart.data.Measure.description:
Definition of a single measure in a chart
chartType binding rules
pie, donut The measure is assigned to feed uid “size”.
scatter The first measure with role “axis1”, or (if not exists) the first measure with role “axis2” or (if not exist) with role “axis3”, is assigned to the feed uid “valueAxis”. The other measure is assigned to feed uid “valueAxis2”.
bubble The first measure with role “axis1”, or (if not exists) the first measure with role “axis2” or (if not exist) with role “axis3”, is assigned to the feed uid “valueAxis”.
The first measure with role “axis2”, or (if not exists) the second measure with role “axis1” or (if not exist) the first measure with role “axis3”, is assigned to the feed uid “valueAxis2”.
The remaining measure is assigned to feed uid “bubbleWidth”.
heatmap The measure is assigned to the feed uid “color”.
treemap The first measure with role “axis1”, or (if not exists) the first measure with role “axis2” or (if not exist) with role “axis3”, is assigned to the feed uid “color”. The other measure is assigned to feed uid “weight”.
..dual.. At least one measure is assigned to each of the feed uids “valueAxis” and “valueAxis2”, according to the general rule.
sap.chart.data.Measure.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new ui5/data/Measure. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getName name} : string
    • {@link #getLabel label} : string
    • {@link #getUnitBinding unitBinding} : string
    • {@link #getValueFormat valueFormat} : string
    • {@link #getRole role} : string (default: axis1)
    • {@link #getSemantics semantics} : sap.chart.data.MeasureSemantics (default: Actual)
    • {@link #getSemanticallyRelatedMeasures semanticallyRelatedMeasures} : object
    • {@link #getAnalyticalInfo analyticalInfo} : object
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.core.Element#constructor sap.ui.core.Element} can be used as well.
sap.chart.data.Measure.helpDescription:
Definition of a single measure in a chart
chartType binding rules
pie, donut The measure is assigned to feed uid “size”.
scatter The first measure with role “axis1”, or (if not exists) the first measure with role “axis2” or (if not exist) with role “axis3”, is assigned to the feed uid “valueAxis”. The other measure is assigned to feed uid “valueAxis2”.
bubble The first measure with role “axis1”, or (if not exists) the first measure with role “axis2” or (if not exist) with role “axis3”, is assigned to the feed uid “valueAxis”.
The first measure with role “axis2”, or (if not exists) the second measure with role “axis1” or (if not exist) the first measure with role “axis3”, is assigned to the feed uid “valueAxis2”.
The remaining measure is assigned to feed uid “bubbleWidth”.
heatmap The measure is assigned to the feed uid “color”.
treemap The first measure with role “axis1”, or (if not exists) the first measure with role “axis2” or (if not exist) with role “axis3”, is assigned to the feed uid “color”. The other measure is assigned to feed uid “weight”.
..dual.. At least one measure is assigned to each of the feed uids “valueAxis” and “valueAxis2”, according to the general rule.

models.description: A map of model instances to which the object should be attached. The models are keyed by their model name. For the default model, String(undefined) is expected.

role.description:
How values of Measure will be rendered in the chart. Possible role values are {@link sap.chart.data.MeasureRoleType axis1}, {@link sap.chart.data.MeasureRoleType axis2}, {@link sap.chart.data.MeasureRoleType axis3}, and {@link sap.chart.data.MeasureRoleType axis4}. The default is {@link sap.chart.data.MeasureRoleType axis1}. They correspond to the well-known concepts of axis identifiers in the Cartesian coordinate system, e.g. a Y-axis in a bar/column/line chart, an X- and a Y-axis in a scatter chart, or two Y-axes in bar charts, and an optional third axis for the weight/size/intensity/temperature of a data point. You can create a new measure as follow: 
...
new sap.chart.data.Measure({name: "MEASURE1", role: sap.chart.data.MeasureRoleType.axis1})
...
Detailed usage of measure role. Please refer to {@link sap.chart.data.MeasureRoleType MeasureRoleType} NOTE: Role definition would not work for Bullet Chart and users need to set semantics instead.

The default is {@link sap.chart.data.MeasureRoleType axis1}. They correspond to the well-known concepts of axis identifiers in the Cartesian coordinate system, e.g. a Y-axis in a bar/column/line chart, an X- and a Y-axis in a scatter chart, or two Y-axes in bar charts, and an optional third axis for the weight/size/intensity/temperature of a data point. sap.chart.data.Dimension.description:
Definition of a single dimension in a chart
chartType binding rules
pie, donut All dimensions are assigned to feed uid “color”.
scatter, bubble All dimensions with role category are assigned to feed uid “shape”.
heatmap All dimensions with role “series” and “category2” are assigned to the feed uid “categoryAxis2”.
treemap All dimensions are assigned to the feed uid “categoryAxis” in the default sequence.
sap.chart.data.Dimension.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new ui5/data/Dimension. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getName name} : string
    • {@link #getLabel label} : string
    • {@link #getTextFormatter textFormatter} : function
    • {@link #getTextProperty textProperty} : string
    • {@link #getDisplayText displayText} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getRole role} : string (default: category)
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.core.Element#constructor sap.ui.core.Element} can be used as well.

sap.chart.data.name: sap.chart.data
sap.chart.data.description: Package with additional chart data APIs
sap.chart.data.helpDescription: Package with additional chart data APIs

sap.chart.data.TimeDimension.description:
Definition of a single time dimension in a chart

If there is exactly one dimension with time semantics, then instead of line, time_line shall be used (implicitly).

TimeDmension is assigned to feed uid "timeAxis".
sap.chart.data.TimeDimension.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new ui5/data/TimeDimension. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getTimeUnit timeUnit} : sap.chart.TimeUnitType
    • {@link #getFiscalYearPeriodCount fiscalYearPeriodCount} : object
    • {@link #getProjectedValueStartTime projectedValueStartTime} : any
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.chart.data.Dimension#constructor sap.chart.data.Dimension} can be used as well.
sap.chart.data.TimeDimension.helpDescription:
Definition of a single time dimension in a chart

If there is exactly one dimension with time semantics, then instead of line, time_line shall be used (implicitly).

TimeDmension is assigned to feed uid "timeAxis".

layoutData.description: Defines the layout constraints for this control when it is used inside a Layout. LayoutData classes are typed classes and must match the embedding Layout. See VariantLayoutData for aggregating multiple alternative LayoutData instances to a single Element.
layoutData.helpDescription: Defines the layout constraints for this control when it is used inside a Layout. LayoutData classes are typed classes and must match the embedding Layout. See VariantLayoutData for aggregating multiple alternative LayoutData instances to a single Element.

tooltip.description:

Can either be an instance of a TooltipBase subclass or a simple string.
tooltip.helpDescription:

textFormatter.description: Function returning a formatted text for a Dimension key value that will be used for axis labelling. If specified, this property takes precedence over the "textProperty" property of the Dimension. Dimension key value and the corresponding text will be passed to the supplied function as parameters.
textFormatter.helpDescription: Function returning a formatted text for a Dimension key value that will be used for axis labelling. If specified, this property takes precedence over the "textProperty" property of the Dimension. Dimension key value and the corresponding text will be passed to the supplied function as parameters.

displayText.description: Whether a text is displayed. If the "textProperty" property has not been specified, it will be derived from the metadata.
displayText.helpDescription: Whether a text is displayed. If the "textProperty" property has not been specified, it will be derived from the metadata.

models.description: A map of model instances to which the object should be attached. The models are keyed by their model name. For the default model, String(undefined) is expected.

role.description:
How the Dimension will influence the chart layout. Possible values are {@link sap.chart.data.DimensionRoleType category}, {@link sap.chart.data.DimensionRoleType series} or {@link sap.chart.data.DimensionRoleType category2}. The default is {@link sap.chart.data.DimensionRoleType category}. You can create a new dimension as follow: 
...
new sap.chart.data.Dimension({name: "DIMENSION1", role: sap.chart.data.DimensionRoleType.category})
...
Detailed usage of dimension role. Please refer to {@link sap.chart.data.DimensionRoleType DimensionRoleType} NOTE: Has no effect if the Dimension is used as inResultDimensions by Chart
role.helpDescription:
How the Dimension will influence the chart layout. Possible values are {@link sap.chart.data.DimensionRoleType category}, {@link sap.chart.data.DimensionRoleType series} or {@link sap.chart.data.DimensionRoleType category2}. id.description: Unique ID of this instance. If not given, a so called autoID will be generated by the framework. AutoIDs use a unique prefix that must not be used for Ids that the application (or other code) creates. It can be configured option 'autoIDPrefix', see {@link sap.ui.core.Configuration}.
